0313|*Space for extra specifications:
0314|*Parameters `speclist' and `specmax' limit the amount of extra
0315|*specifications. When a Survo operation is activated, all specification
0316|*text (consisting of specifications in the curren subfield and in the
0317|*potential *GLOBAL* subfield) are collected to a list having a length of
0318|*`speclist' characters at most and consisting of `specmax' items at most.
0319|*Example: speclist=1000000 specmax=10000
0321|*In SURVO MM values of parameters speclist and specmax are defined
0322|*automatically.
0324|*Using very large edit fields (say over 20000 lines) in SURVO MM
0325|*may slow down certain activities depending on specifications.
0326|*To increase the speed in such situations automatic detection of
0327|*proper speclist and specmax values may be overridden by setting
0328|*the 1st control character (in front of the 1st edit line) to ' ' (space).
0329|*Then values given in SURVO.APU (or altered by SYSTEM commands)
0330|*will be valid. Also extra border lines in suitable places
0331|*speeds up operations when the first control character is ' '.
