0520|*alarm (system parameter in SURVO.APU):
0521|*Parameter `alarm' gives the time in the form 09:15:30 for an alarm. When
0522|*the clock of the computer reaches this time point, the user is alarmed
0523|*by a beep and by a message
0524|SALARM!!!   Press #
S   | 5555555555555555555
0526|*The message stays until the user presses the # key. Survo alarms only
0527|*when it is updating the clock on the top line of the edit field. Thus,
0528|*an alarm may be delayed when a long Survo function is operating.
0529|*Example: alarm=09:15 .
0531|*An alarm can be set temporarily (valid during current Survo session only) by
0532|*SYSTEM alarm=hh:mm:ss
0534|*To set a permanent alarm, insert a line of type
0535|*alarm=hh:mm:ss
0536|*in the SURVO.APU file.
